                    },
                    "body": "We never did get to the bottom of if we could configure jemalloc in such a way that it wouldn't do this, though we've changed the default for macOS to mimalloc so it shouldn't be impacting people (**and** AFAIK most typically shows up in benchmarking scenarios with lots of quick iterations, not in real-world scenarios).\r\n\r\nI'm fine with closing it, though (as a note to possible future selves) it's not fully resolved.",
